@baseUrl = http://localhost:3000/api

### Register a new user
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "fullName": "Test User",
    "email": "testuser6@example.com",
    "password": "Password123!",
    "confirmPassword": "Password123!",
    "householdSize": 2,
    "dietaryPreferences": ["Vegetarian", "Gluten-Free"],
    "budgetRange": "Medium",
    "location": "San Francisco, CA"
}

### Get CSRF Token (Required for Login)
# @name csrf
GET {{baseUrl}}/auth/csrf

### Login (NextAuth Credentials)
# Note: NextAuth requires a CSRF token. The variable below captures it from the previous request.
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/callback/credentials
Content-Type: application/x-www-form-urlencoded

# csrfToken={{csrf.response.body.csrfToken}}&email=testuser@example.com&password=Password123!&json=true
